License: Released under GPLv2

Indexes a directory of documents (emails).
Creates a database of the form: word -> list of emails containing the word.
This allows to search words faster.

Tested on email database: http://www.cs.cmu.edu/~enron/enron_mail_20110402.tgz


Hystory:

After using intern() function (32bits system):
Indexing 125K of emails requires  82M of RAM (keeping 300K of words)
Indexing 500K of emails requires 275M of RAM (keeping 580K of words)

Initial results (64bits system):
Indexing 125K of emails requires 160M of RAM (keeping 300K of words)
Indexing 500K of emails requires 540M of RAM (keeping 580K of words)

